Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.71,0:02:35.38,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Ruri Torakura (38)\NAsanobu's Wife
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.71,0:02:39.13,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Kishiharu Torakura (45)\NThird Son of the Torakura Family
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.38,0:02:43.18,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Jōhei Hagawa (29)\NKamiyo's Boyfriend
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.43,0:02:52.98,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Asanobu Torakura (52)\NSecond son of the Torakura family
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.11,0:02:58.11,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Mina Torakura (26)\NSecond daughter of the Torakura family
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.92,0:03:25.18,Character Card,,10,10,0,,Rikushige Koga (71)\NTorakura Family Butler
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.70,0:03:57.92,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Hikaru Hinohara (24)\NTorakura Family Maid
Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.50,0:00:07.44,Narration Off,,10,10,0,,{\be10}We got suspicious about Inspector Ōtaki's strange behaviour, and ended up going with him to a western-style mansion hidden in a forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.99,0:00:13.70,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}There, a group of siblings in a rather uneasy mood gathered together to discuss their inheritance.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.84,0:00:20.33,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}While the master of the mansion was missing, they tried to take a family photo,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.69,0:00:24.98,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}but the master, who wasn't supposed to be there, was captured on it in an ominous state.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.49,0:00:30.76,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Seeking comprehensive answers, he clears all mysteries and codes!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.76,0:00:34.47,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The mystery grows ever deeper.\NWill the Dracula case ever be solved?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.47,0:00:36.05,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}He sees the single truth for what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.05,0:00:38.18,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}and looks like a kid but has the mind of an adult!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.18,0:00:40.27,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}His name? Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.23,0:02:31.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait, what is this?! It's almost like ghost photography!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.89,0:02:35.38,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Why's brother-in-law in this photo? He wasn't there at the time!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.38,0:02:39.13,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,I have no idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.13,0:02:43.18,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me — you did something to the photo when you developed it, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.56,0:02:48.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't be stupid! You can't pull a trick like that with analogue film this quickly!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.64,0:02:52.54,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,T-Then did Brother really turn into a vampire, like the rumours said?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.54,0:02:54.16,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,That's ridiculous!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.16,0:02:58.11,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Vampires don't exist outside of stuff like horror movies and novels!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.10,0:03:04.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Him disappearing from the casket and the ghost photo were tricks that Hakuya-{\i1}niisan{\i0} set up!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.32,0:03:07.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't think so.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.56,0:03:10.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The master's in the same place where the girls said they saw him.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.34,0:03:15.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And I think they really {\i1}did {\i0}see him there back then.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.93,0:03:25.18,Dialogue Top,,10,10,0,,Either way, it would be prudent to find the master at once and have him explain the circumstances behind these incidents to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.57,0:03:26.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.00,0:03:27.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.34,0:03:30.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, mind if we borrow that photo for a bit?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.54,0:03:37.44,Dialogue,,10,10,0,,We want to take it to the kitchen to have Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r} and Kazuha{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r} confirm whether the photo matches what they saw.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.09,0:03:42.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And they ain't here, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.48,0:03:44.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The chefs are gone, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.04,0:03:49.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right now, they're all probably eating in another room.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.52,0:03:54.61,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,We maids usually eat with them, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.48,0:03:57.92,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Since I was searching for the master, I missed it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.92,0:04:03.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I remember correctly, you were the child that the master's fiancée brought with her, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.68,0:04:04.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.99,0:04:06.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How did your mother die?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.62,0:04:09.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I heard it was an accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.29,0:04:16.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But at the time I was hospitalised in the master's hospital due to a weak constitution, so I don't know the details...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.33,0:04:19.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The master worked at a hospital?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.96,0:04:23.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. He was the director of Torakura General Hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.90,0:04:31.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was very kind. He even paid for my hospitalisation and surgery fees!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.27,0:04:36.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So he's the reason you work as a maid here?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.59,0:04:37.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.70,0:04:41.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm looking after the master who my mother was going to marry!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.30,0:04:47.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, what actually happened was that half a year ago, back when I was unemployed after graduating from university,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.33,0:04:52.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I got an invitation from the master saying 'there's an opening as a maid, so won't you come?'
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.99,0:04:55.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why I'm not used to this mansion yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.77,0:05:03.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This morning, even though the master called for me, I didn't know which room, so I ended up standing him up.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.35,0:05:06.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So the master's going to be mad when we find him, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.66,0:05:11.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I-It's fine! He's never been mad at me since I came here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.92,0:05:15.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Though the others do complain about him being too strict at checking the cleaning.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.50,0:05:18.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It{\i1} is{\i0} a pretty shoddy job, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.24,0:05:22.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look here, at the floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.14,0:05:24.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's flour or something all over!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.34,0:05:28.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that those girls' doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.09,0:05:33.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I told them there weren't any gyōza skins, they said they'd make some themselves
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.94,0:05:36.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and asked where the bread and wheat flours were...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.79,0:05:38.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They probably spilled some since they were in a rush.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.55,0:05:42.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After all, they placed the cloth for the finished skins on their lap and bundled them into clingfilm.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.31,0:05:45.65,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The first thing to come to mind with garlic were gyōza, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.04,0:05:48.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But what's this wide gap here?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.87,0:05:54.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See, for about fifty centimetres, there isn't any flour!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.54,0:05:56.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As if something'd been dragged through here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.85,0:05:58.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Speaking of which...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.81,0:06:04.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I told those girls that there might still be a bag of garlic in the storeroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.18,0:06:11.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If they'd dragged that bag here, then they'd probably still be here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.10,0:06:14.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I found the garlic, Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.35,0:06:17.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wow, there's so much!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.08,0:06:18.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh no...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.49,0:06:22.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It already started sproutin' and growin' roots...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.04,0:06:23.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't worry!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.46,0:06:26.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It won't taste as good, but you can still eat it as long as you cut them off.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.11,0:06:30.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But are we going to be okay with just garlic?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.35,0:06:32.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I got this, so we're covered!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.47,0:06:34.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A-A cross?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.79,0:06:38.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah! It's made from a silver knife and spoon so it's super effective!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.62,0:06:44.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But for this kind of thing to work, don't you have to be a devout Christian?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.19,0:06:47.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's fine! Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}, you celebrate Christmas, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.79,0:06:52.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We celebrate Christ's birthday every year, so it's gotta work!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.78,0:06:56.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.93,0:07:04.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?! Type AB? The blood found inside the casket the master was sleeping in really was type AB?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.33,0:07:05.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.79,0:07:12.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} put in a good word and had the Gunma prefecture police examine it, and there's no doubt it was type AB.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.25,0:07:18.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But according to the folks here at the mansion, the master's blood type...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.05,0:07:19.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's type A.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.35,0:07:24.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When the master was younger, he suffered a serious injury.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.53,0:07:30.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I still remember that we were given the honour of him using our type A blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.60,0:07:32.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then whose blood was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.94,0:07:40.18,Dialogue,,10,10,0,,I believe the only one with type AB blood associated with this mansion was the maid Shimizu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who passed away half a year ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.53,0:07:41.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say what?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.38,0:07:47.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why would the blood of someone who died half a year ago be in that casket?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.48,0:07:53.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me brother-in-law kept her blood and was drinking it inside the casket!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.86,0:08:00.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shouldn't that blood be examinated for stuff like DNA?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.87,0:08:04.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And? Is it still gonna take long for the tunnel to be fixed?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.00,0:08:08.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. We told them we'd like to be able to cross it before morning, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.31,0:08:11.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And if anything happens to my daughter before then, there'll be {\i1}hell{\i0} to pay, you hear me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.06,0:08:14.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's fine, don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.85,0:08:17.93,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The girls are distracted makin' gyōza anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.34,0:08:20.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And what about the master?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.06,0:08:22.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Still haven't found him.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.12,0:08:25.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even though we looked just about everywhere...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.64,0:08:27.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did Asa-{\i1}nii{\i0} say anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.42,0:08:34.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He says he called brother-in-law's mobile a bunch of times, but it kept going to voicemail.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.37,0:08:36.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And? Where's he now?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.25,0:08:38.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sure he's in the smoking room taking a puff.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.92,0:08:43.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think Hakuya-{\i1}niisan{\i0} left his mobile phone somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.14,0:08:49.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's up?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.18,0:08:51.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I-It's an e-mail.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.96,0:08:53.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,From Hakuya-{\i1}niisan{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.82,0:08:58.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It says, 'I'll tell everyone my answer, so gather in the dining room'.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.34,0:09:02.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then this was a group mail?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.91,0:09:04.60,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}A group mail?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.28,0:09:15.03,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}In the end, the guy still ain't shown up.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.79,0:09:17.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Looks like we're gonna get some rain.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.68,0:09:21.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, aren't you worried?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.54,0:09:25.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You still haven't found Kamiyo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neesan{\r}, have you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.53,0:09:30.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My honey's the kind who'd suddenly take off somewhere on a whim.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.54,0:09:34.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You'd better keep a tight grip on her. She's your sugar mama, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.36,0:09:39.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, if she dumps me, I can just hook up with you again.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.88,0:09:42.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Asa-{\i1}nii{\i0}, how long are you going to be smoking for, man?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.26,0:09:48.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me he didn't get brother-in-law's message since he changed phones.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.66,0:09:51.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.64,0:09:55.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,J-Just now, there was a strange shadow at the window.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.59,0:09:56.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A strange shadow?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.34,0:10:06.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me brother really...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.34,0:10:07.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-Turned into a vampire...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.24,0:10:10.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-There's no way!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.01,0:10:16.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's got to be using a rope or something to be lowered upside-down like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.40,0:10:22.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A-Are you serious?! He disappeared into the sky!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.98,0:10:25.27,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That's ridiculous. It's not humanly possible!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.51,0:10:27.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-Hold on, that over there...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.52,0:10:37.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-Hey, Hattori, what's {\i1}that{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.87,0:10:40.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I-It's a bird, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.58,0:10:44.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,B-But isn't it a little too big to be a bird?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.58,0:10:48.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kudō?! You're bleedin', man!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.31,0:10:50.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way, you weren't bitten by something, were you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.71,0:10:53.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you talking about? I just got rained on a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.59,0:10:56.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That ain't rain.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.48,0:10:59.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The roof! There's blood drippin' from the roof!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.70,0:11:01.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's above here? Are there any rooms?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.33,0:11:03.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.52,0:11:05.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the attic, there's a smoking room.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.57,0:11:07.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-What is this about the smoking room?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.18,0:11:09.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The blood's probably dripping down from there!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.29,0:11:11.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It can't be...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.23,0:11:13.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wasn't Asa-{\i1}nii{\i0} in there?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.56,0:11:27.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's no good. His carotid artery's been cut. He's dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.49,0:11:32.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's holding the knife himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.14,0:11:32.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that means...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.47,0:11:38.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was going to be attacked by someone, and took his own life instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.83,0:11:39.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Or...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.24,0:11:43.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Someone wanted it to {\i1}look{\i0} that way...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.65,0:11:46.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which one was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.34,0:11:55.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dear?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.09,0:12:00.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, I've got to hurry up and find my honey, or...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.19,0:12:08.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right. Kamiyo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neesan{\r} might've already been taken by the vampirised Hakuya-{\i1}niisan{\i0},
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.64,0:12:11.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and hung upside down from a stake, like in the legends.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.80,0:12:13.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey, hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.64,0:12:14.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.30,0:12:17.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could you tell us about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.14,0:12:19.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,About that legend.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.12,0:12:24.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The master said it was a story from the Edo period.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.49,0:12:30.30,Dialogue,,10,10,0,,The feudal lord who once governed this area was an ancestor of the Torakura family. It's said that he was dearly loved by his people.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.75,0:12:37.69,Dialogue,,10,10,0,,However, at the time, rumours began to surface about the possibility of the childless feudal lord yielding the fiefdom to his younger brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.69,0:12:42.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, the feudal lord suddenly invited a beautiful woman to the castle to take the role of a concubine.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.88,0:12:48.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That concubine happily gave birth to an heir, and everyone at the castle was relieved. However...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.86,0:12:51.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One stormy night, an incident occurred...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.29,0:12:52.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An incident?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.61,0:13:00.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The story goes that the concubine fell from a cliff and was found with her abdomen pierced by a tree branch.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.59,0:13:09.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thinking it odd, the feudal lord used tools he obtained from some foreigners to torture the concubine's aides.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.57,0:13:12.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And so, the truth came to light.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.63,0:13:20.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They told him that they'd tricked the concubine by telling her that the young prince hadn't returned from the forest yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.50,0:13:29.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Enraged, the feudal lord impaled his younger brother and his subordinates in the same way the concubine had been impaled,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.87,0:13:33.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and lined them up in the same forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.59,0:13:38.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ever since, it seems that feudal lord's been called 'Lord Impaler'.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.54,0:13:44.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But that doesn't fit with being a vampire, does it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.64,0:13:53.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't you know? The model for Count Dracula,\NVlad III of Wallachia, impaled all who opposed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.45,0:13:56.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's known as 'The Impaling Prince'.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.69,0:13:58.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,R-Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.44,0:14:03.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. Vlad III's father was 'Prince Dracul'...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.84,0:14:07.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...so as his son, he was called 'Dracula'.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.95,0:14:12.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now that you've heard the story, would you like to take a look at the foreign torture room?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.67,0:14:13.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Foreign torture room?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.26,0:14:19.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.00,0:14:24.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That feudal lord kept the tools he bought from foreigners in this room.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.19,0:14:27.17,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}There's even a guillotine!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.88,0:14:29.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see! It was this room!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.02,0:14:36.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Remember, the master called for me this morning, but I didn't know where the torture room was.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.34,0:14:39.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Couldn't you have just asked someone?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.82,0:14:44.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, the master said 'come to the foreign torture room without telling anyone'.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.64,0:14:49.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He particularly didn't want the butler noticing.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.60,0:14:56.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course, when you guys looked for the master, you searched this room too, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.32,0:15:00.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was creepy, so I skipped it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.84,0:15:09.96,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}With all of this 'Lord Impaler' stuff, this torture room and that flying monster, we better not let the girls know about this.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.36,0:15:13.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And done! The {\i1}gyōza{\i0} are all wrapped!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.39,0:15:14.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We sure made a lot!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.64,0:15:17.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now we just gotta cook 'em!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.71,0:15:19.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We have to let Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} and the others have some, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.99,0:15:20.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.74,0:15:26.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.72,0:15:31.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We just wanted to say that if you're going to use the stove, make sure to turn it off when you're done.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.86,0:15:33.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,R-Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.14,0:15:34.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We know.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.64,0:15:35.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Good luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.92,0:15:40.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Should we really keep quiet about this murder?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.19,0:15:44.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They're better off not knowing.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.13,0:15:44.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.91,0:15:49.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okay, you guys!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.62,0:15:54.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Until we come back, none of you four are to leave this dining room!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.80,0:15:56.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But we have to find my honey!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.14,0:16:00.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Leave that to us and the butler.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.70,0:16:03.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Call us if anything happens, Hikaru{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.53,0:16:04.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y-Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.10,0:16:11.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You {\i1}did{\i0} tell all the other maids and chefs to stay in the same room, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.96,0:16:15.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. But our opponent is a vampire.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.96,0:16:19.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Can we really go just the three of us against him?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.61,0:16:23.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't be stupid! There ain't no such thing as vampires!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.88,0:16:26.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And we're going to find proof of that right now!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.81,0:16:30.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's start with this casket.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.50,0:16:34.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's gotta be some mechanism to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.88,0:16:40.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Also, doesn't something feel different in this room from the first time we came here?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.34,0:16:44.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the rug and the sofa are in the same place...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.47,0:16:49.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, right, speaking of the casket. When that incident took place half a year ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.58,0:16:53.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,it seems the master asked the chef to wake him up.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.06,0:16:57.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ain't that the kind of thing you usually ask a maid or the butler?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.49,0:17:02.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think the master didn't trust me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.47,0:17:08.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After all, he'd make a suspicious face whenever I expressed disapproval at his odd actions.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.04,0:17:10.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, look at this.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.40,0:17:13.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The rug's cut in two places!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.34,0:17:25.23,Dialogue,,10,10,0,,Which means that if you pull this here, take this portion out, and put the ends together again, the rug becomes smaller, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.23,0:17:26.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.74,0:17:32.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So basically, when we came in, the coffin was closer to the centre of the room, over—
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.29,0:17:35.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A handle on the tiles?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.00,0:17:41.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see. It was this kind of trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.15,0:17:46.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next up, that ghost photo.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.59,0:17:50.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We've more or less figured that out, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.27,0:17:53.21,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I knew it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.69,0:17:57.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, do they always use this wall as the backdrop when they take pictures?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.58,0:18:00.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. The chairs are also in approximately the same positions.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.72,0:18:06.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In this instance, I understand the two young girls pressed the shutter button on the camera,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.18,0:18:11.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but the master had actually asked the maid, Hikaru{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.03,0:18:13.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.25,0:18:15.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.19,0:18:19.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It used to always be done by the maid who passed away, Shimizu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.89,0:18:26.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe he just figured that'd be her role, since she replaced Shimizu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.99,0:18:30.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, that maid seems to have incurred the master's favour.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.34,0:18:34.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hikaru{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} said it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.26,0:18:37.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That the master was very kind and never got mad at her.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.12,0:18:40.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-That's preposterous!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.45,0:18:45.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The only things to come out of the master's mouth about her recently have been complaints!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.59,0:18:49.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But she said she was invited by the master to this mansion!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.99,0:18:51.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nothing of the sort!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.40,0:18:57.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The master said she came here crying, using her status as his former fiancée's daughter to beg him to hire her.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.40,0:19:06.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Though she really is a very cheery girl, and the maids and chefs seem to love her.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.59,0:19:11.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But if she's saying that kind of nonsense, then she must've come here with some sort of ulterior motive.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.50,0:19:12.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ulterior motive?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.94,0:19:17.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Has she told you about her mother, Yōko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.71,0:19:20.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that she passed away because of an unfortunate accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.02,0:19:23.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was a stormy night when she passed away.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.72,0:19:29.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yōko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r} suddenly said she was going to drive to the master's hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.71,0:19:32.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I said it was dangerous and tried to stop her,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.22,0:19:36.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but sure enough, she drove through a guardrail on the mountain path and fell off the cliff with the car.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.89,0:19:41.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,According to the police, it was driver error due to low visibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.05,0:19:43.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why would she do that on a day like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.48,0:19:48.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just before she left, the master called.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.40,0:19:54.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He told me to tell Yōko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r} that her daughter's surgery was a success.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.12,0:20:02.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So the maid Shimizu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} said that she probably wanted to meet with her daughter as soon as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.77,0:20:07.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But at the time, Yōko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r} looked pale and didn't seem like that at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.14,0:20:09.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why Shimizu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.01,0:20:15.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I instructed her to pass the master's message to Yōko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.06,0:20:19.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was that car Yōko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.76,0:20:24.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, it belonged to the deceased Asanobu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.68,0:20:28.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That day was the 13th anniversary of the former master's death, so everyone was at the mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.37,0:20:31.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By 'everyone', you mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.39,0:20:32.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.21,0:20:38.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Everyone that gathered here today was there.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.22,0:20:43.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So if that accident, like the one in the legend, was planned by someone...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.83,0:20:46.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,D-Does Hikaru{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} know about this?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.38,0:20:47.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.94,0:20:52.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The master instructed me not to tell her.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.06,0:20:54.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I believed he meant to tell her himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.17,0:21:00.13,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Hikaru{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10} was summoned by the master.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.13,0:21:01.52,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}She said she didn't want to meet him, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.89,0:21:04.70,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}If that was a lie, and she really {\i1}did{\i0} meet him...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.27,0:21:08.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where's Hikaru{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.78,0:21:09.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She's not here, is she?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.11,0:21:13.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She said she was going to refill the tea.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.29,0:21:14.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She went to the kitchen.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.04,0:21:15.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The kitchen?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.29,0:21:20.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyway, aren't the police here yet? You {\i1}did{\i0} call them, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.29,0:21:24.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, but they said the tunnel would take until morning to fix.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.09,0:21:27.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you find my honey yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.51,0:21:28.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.26,0:21:31.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm hungry.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.37,0:21:35.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe I should have some of the {\i1}gyōza{\i0} the girls made.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.29,0:21:39.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How did you know the girls were making {\i1}gyōza{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.99,0:21:42.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They came here earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.44,0:21:45.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They came to borrow the freezer from Hikaru{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.06,0:21:48.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They wanted to freeze the extra {\i1}gyōza{\i0} they'd made, so they wanted to put them in the freezer.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.12,0:21:55.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah, after they borrowed the key, Hikaru{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} basically followed them to the kitchen, didn't she?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.55,0:21:57.62,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That's right! There's one place...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.02,0:21:59.83,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}...that hasn't been searched yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.56,0:22:01.39,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The freezer!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.06,0:22:03.47,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Could it be that inside...?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.79,0:22:09.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's no good. This ain't the right key, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.71,0:22:13.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wish it had labels saying which key is for what.
